body: I did not make any other changes and it worked normally before.

@glenn-jocher is adding multi thread option for the dataloader to speed up training up to 4 times (depending on your CPU), the problem is that there is a bug with the label accuracy, but he is working on it and I'm also trying to find the problem. I would recommend using an older version of the repo.
@Jaiczay Can you suggest an latest stable version for us? I'm training and getting some problem.

@kaaier detect.py works as intended. If your output is not to your liking it is due to your model.

```bash
# Detect
sudo rm -rf yolov3 && git clone https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3
cd yolov3 && python3 detect.py
```
![zidane](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/26833433/54822739-43619580-4cae-11e9-8391-4440fdc39497.jpg)

@WannaSeaU single GPU training works as intended currently.
@glenn-jocher  For single GPU training, is the argument --num_workers  supposed to be 1?

the model is official yolov3.weights，but it may be wrong with output
